title: Saborio scores in extra time; DC United secures playoff spot
text:
Saborio scores in 92nd minute; DC United beats New York City FC 2-1 to secure playoff spot THE ASSOCIATED PRESS   9:14   9:15   
People: 
New York (1742) 

WASHINGTON — Alvaro Saborio knocked in a loose ball on a free kick in the 92nd minute and D.C. United beat New York City FC 2-1 on a rainy Friday night to secure an Eastern Conference playoff spot. 
D.C. United (14-12-6) snapped its six-game winless stretch to move into a first-place tie with the New York Red Bulls. NYC FC (10-15-7) had its three-game winning streak stopped. 
Frank Lampard opened the scoring in the first minute for the fastest goal in NYC FC's first season. Bill Hamid blocked David Villa's fast-break attempt and Lampard slotted the rebound for his third goal in his last four games. 
Fabian Espindola tied it in the 73rd minute. Josh Saunders dove to get a hand on Chris Pontius' shot and Espindola put in the rebound. 
Villa sent a ball just over the crossbar in the 41st and rolled one wide of the near post in first-half stoppage time.
